<p>I have a problem with one exercise. Task is to find all subsets within the array which have a sum equal to N and print them. Also I need to find all unique subsets and this is the problem. I am using Gray method to find all combinations but some of them are duplicated. Here's my code:</p>  <pre><code>    int matchSum = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());     int[] numbers = Console.ReadLine().Split().Select(int.Parse).ToArray();     int combinations = (int) Math.Pow(2, numbers.Length);     List&lt;int&gt; currentSequence = new List&lt;int&gt;();      bool foundMatch = false;      for (int i = 1; i &lt; combinations; i++)     {         for (int bit = 0; bit &lt; Convert.ToString(i,2).Length; bit++)         {             int mask = (i &gt;&gt; bit) &amp; 1;             if (mask == 1)             {                 currentSequence.Add(numbers[numbers.Length-bit-1]);             }         }         if (currentSequence.Sum() == matchSum)         {             Console.WriteLine("{0} = {1}", string.Join(" + ", currentSequence), matchSum);             foundMatch = true;         }         currentSequence.Clear();     }      if (!foundMatch)     {         Console.WriteLine("No matching subsets.");     } </code></pre>  <p>Best regards!</p>